claim.claim-text:
1. A method of reducing a dopant diffusion rate in a doped semiconductor region comprising:
selecting a plurality of impurity elements including at least one dopant element; including:
selecting a first impurity element with a first atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a second impurity element with a second atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a third impurity element with a third atomic radius that is different from the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting amounts of each impurity element of the plurality of impurity elements wherein amounts and atomic radii of each of the plurality of impurity elements are selected to provide an average impurity element atomic radius over the doped semiconductor region that is substantially the same as the average host matrix atomic radius;
introducing the plurality of impurity elements to a selected region of the host matrix; and
annealing the selected region of the host matrix.

12. A method of forming a transistor comprising:
forming a pair of source/drain regions spaced apart by a channel region; including selecting a plurality of impurity elements having at least one dopant element, wherein formation of the source/drain regions includes:
selecting a first impurity element with a first atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a second impurity element with a second atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a third impurity element with a third atomic radius that is different from the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting amounts of each impurity element of the plurality of impurity elements wherein amounts and atomic radii of each of the plurality of impurity elements are selected to provide an average impurity element atomic radius over the doped semiconductor region that is substantially the same as the average host matrix atomic radius;
introducing the plurality of impurity elements to selected regions of the host matrix;
annealing the pair of source/drain regions of the semiconductor surface; and

forming a gate adjacent to the channel region.

18. A method of forming a memory device comprising:
forming a number of memory cells on a semiconductor substrate, wherein forming each memory cell includes:
introducing first and second impurity elements to a selected region of the semiconductor surface, the first impurity element has an atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius of the semiconductor region, the second impurity element has an atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius of the semiconductor region;
wherein a first impurity element atomic fraction is substantially equal to (RH- R2)/[(R1-RH)+(RH-R2)], where RH is the average host matrix size, R1 is the first impurity element size, and R2 is the second impurity element size;
wherein a second impurity element atomic fraction is substantially equal to 1 minus the first impurity element atomic fraction;

annealing the selected region of the semiconductor surface;
forming a number of bitlines coupled to each memory cell;
forming a number of wordlines coupled to each memory cell; and
forming a number of sourcelines coupled to each memory cell.

21. A method of forming an information handling system comprising:
forming a processor;
forming a memory device, including:
forming a number of memory cells on a semiconductor substrate, wherein forming each memory cell includes:
introducing first and second impurity elements to a selected region of the semiconductor surface, the first impurity element has an atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius of the semiconductor region, the second impurity element has an atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius of the semiconductor region;
wherein a first impurity element atomic fraction is substantially equal to (RH-R2)/[(R1-RH)+(RH-R2)], where RH is the average host matrix size, R1 is the first impurity element size, and R2 is the second impurity element size;
wherein a second impurity element atomic fraction is substantially equal to 1 minus the first impurity element atomic fraction;
annealing the selected region of the semiconductor surface;

forming a number of bitlines, wordlines and sourcelines coupled to each memory cell; and

forming a bus coupled between the processor and the memory device.

26. A method of reducing a dopant diffusion rate in a doped semiconductor region comprising:
selecting a plurality of impurity elements including:
selecting a first impurity element with a first atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a second impurity element with a second atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a third impurity element with a third atomic radius that is different from the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting amounts of each impurity element of the plurality of impurity elements wherein amounts and atomic radii of each of the plurality of impurity elements are selected to provide an average impurity element atomic radius over the doped semiconductor region that is substantially the same as the average host matrix atomic radius;

wherein at least two of the plurality of impurity elements are of opposite conductivity types;
selecting an amount of one of the plurality of impurity elements to be larger than the other amounts to produce a net charge effect;
introducing the plurality of impurity elements to a selected region of the host matrix; and
annealing the selected region of the host matrix.

30. A method of reducing a dopant diffusion rate in a doped semiconductor region comprising:
electing a plurality of impurity elements including:
selecting a first impurity element with a first atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a second impurity element with a second atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a third impurity element with a third atomic radius that is different from the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting amounts of each impurity element of the plurality of impurity elements wherein amounts and atomic radii of each of the plurality of impurity elements are selected to provide an average impurity element atomic radius over the doped semiconductor region that is substantially the same as the average host matrix atomic radius;
wherein one of the plurality of impurity elements includes a dopant element and at least one of the plurality of impurity elements includes an electrically inactive element;

introducing the plurality of impurity elements to a selected region of the host matrix; and
annealing the selected region of the host matrix.

33. A method of reducing a dopant diffusion rate in a doped semiconductor region comprising:
selecting a plurality of impurity means including at least one dopant means; including:
selecting a first impurity means with a first atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting a second impurity means with a second atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius; selecting a third impurity means with a third atomic radius that is different from the average host matrix atomic radius;
selecting amounts of each impurity means of the plurality of impurity means wherein amounts and atomic radii of each of the plurality of impurity means are selected to provide an average impurity element atomic radius over the doped semiconductor region that is substantially the same as the average host matrix atomic radius;

introducing the plurality of impurity means to a selected region of the semiconductor host matrix; and
annealing the selected region of the semiconductor host matrix.

37. A method of reducing a dopant diffusion rate in a doped semiconductor region comprising:
introducing first and second impurity elements to the semiconductor region, the first impurity element has an atomic radius larger than an average host matrix atomic radius of the semiconductor region, the second impurity element has an atomic radius smaller than the average host matrix atomic radius of the semiconductor region;
wherein a first impurity element atomic fraction is substantially equal to (RH-R2)/[(R1-RH)+(RH-R2)], where RH is the average host matrix size, R1 is the first impurity element size, and R2 is the second impurity element size;
wherein a second impurity element atomic fraction is substantially equal to 1 minus the first impurity element atomic fraction;

annealing the semiconductor region; and defining a controlled annealing diffusion profile, and locating a semiconductor structure adjacent to the semiconductor region using the controlled diffusion profile.
